  "text": "The proof of Theorem 2 is long and it is omitted in this conference version of the paper due to the page limitation. Interested readers can refer to the full version of this paper [CITATION_1] Example 1. We take the graph in Fig. 2 as an example to illustrate the first-fit scheduling algorithm FFBSD-Pr. The network consists of eight nodes as shown in the figure. In this example, we assume that all eight nodes have uniform beaconing radius normalized to and uniform interference radius equal to = 1 for simplicity. Then the interference graph is exactly the square of the communication graph shown in Fig. 2 . That is, two nodes in are directly connected if and only if they are at most two-hop away in the communication topology.",
